{
    fun greet()
    {
        Console.print( Hello! I am a Calculator! );
    }

    fun sum(a, b)
    {
        return a + b;
    }
}  In function  sum() , variables  a  and  b  hold the input data and are only visible inside the function.  Now, let's create a program that uses this  Calculator . Remember that the functions defined above can be called by any object, including  Application :  object  Application 
{
    calculator = spawn( Calculator );

    state  main 
    {
        // greet the user
        calculator.greet();

        // do some computation
        result = calculator.sum(5, 7);
        Console.print(result);

        // we're done!
        Application.exit();
    }
}  The output of the above program is:  Hello! I am a Calculator!
